        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(android/chat): filter cron-delivery noise and strip <final> wrapper",
        "body": "## Summary\n- filters Android chat history entries that are cron delivery completion markers (\"A cron job ... just completed successfully\") so they do not render as user messages\n- strips top-level `<final>...</final>` wrapping from text message content before rendering\n- keeps scope in the Android view/controller layer only; no protocol or server changes\n\n## Problem\nAndroid currently renders two classes of non-user-visible control/system artifacts:\n1. Cron delivery completion marker messages can appear in history as if they were normal user messages.\n2. Some model outputs arrive wrapped in `<final>...</final>` control tags that should not be shown to users.\n\n## Fix\n- Add `isCronDeliveryNoise(...)` and skip those entries during history parsing.\n- Normalize text content in `parseMessageContent(...)` by removing a top-level `<final>...</final>` wrapper when present.\n\n## Verification\n- manual verification on Android device\n- upstream CI for Android project\n\n## Notes\nIf maintainers prefer either behavior behind a preference flag, I can follow up with a small opt-in/opt-out setting patch.\n\nMade with [Cursor](https://cursor.com)",
